[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer‐detected heap‐buffer‐overflow was triggered during fuzz testing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof libexif’s data‐loading routines. The fuzzer `exif_from_data_fuzzer` invoked [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` in `exif-data.c`, which performed a multi‐byte read [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mvia `memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m beyond the bounds of a heap buffer. The overflow occurs when [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempting to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes immediately past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m‐byte allocation.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A heap‐buffer‐overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mout‐of‐bounds read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in libexif.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Triggering Context  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The crash was found under AddressSanitizer while running `exif_from_data_fuzzer` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith libFuzzer. The fuzzer fed a crafted testcase to `[0m[1;35mexif_data_new_from_data[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich calls `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinally `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fault Location  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  In `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a `memcpy` reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes at an address just beyond a heap‐allocated region of [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes, causing a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti‐byte‐read heap‐buffer‐overflow.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call Stack  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:531[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy`  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant Observations  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The faulty read is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the valid buffer end.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The heap allocation occurs moments before the overflow, indicating a mismatch [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbetween allocated size and read length.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzz harness simply passes raw input to the EXIF parsing routines; it is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot the root cause but the entry point for discovering the defect.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The memory‐allocation logic and buffer‐length calculations in [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Surrounding routines in `exif-data.c`: `exif_data_load_data_content`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data`, and `exif_data_new_from_data`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any parsing or validation steps that determine how many bytes are read into [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach EXIF tag or data entry.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The mechanism by which input lengths and offsets from the EXIF structure are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterpreted to size buffers.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer `exif_from_data_fuzzer` triggers an AddressSanitizer [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s `exif_data_load_data_entry`. The crash occurs [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen a memcpy reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes beyond a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocated region. A patch was [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted in `libexif/exif-data.c` to replace two separate bounds checks with a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle combined check:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow is still reported at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline shifted from [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m209[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle combined check did not prevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer command: `[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mexif_from_data_fuzzer[0m[39m -[0m[33mrss_limit_mb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m2560[0m[39m -[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m25[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash: AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow when `__asan_memcpy` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalled from `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The memcpy reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, which lies exactly one [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace highlights four layers in libexif:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_entry  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_content  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. exif_data_new_from_data  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified `libexif/exif-data.c` around line [0m[1;36m194[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removed two separate sanity checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff >= size` and `s > size - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaced them with one combined condition checking `doff + s > size`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Logging message updated to report the sum `doff + s` and the buffer `size`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPost-Patch Behavior  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer re-run with same settings still triggers an AddressSanitizer [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash site moved slightly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline number changed from [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m209[0m[39m due to patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe nature of the overflow is identical: a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte copy overruns the allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer by one byte.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack and allocation context remain the same as before the patch.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `exif_data_load_data_entry`: how `offset` and `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are computed from the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTIFF tag entry, and whether those fields can wrap or be maliciously large.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `exif_data_load_data_content`: the logic that iterates over directory entries [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand invokes `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definitions of data types and endianness conversions that determine `s` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff`.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation routine `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and how it adjusts the returned[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer size relative to the requested `s`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Surrounding code handling IFD [0m[1;39m([0m[39mImage File Directory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m parsing, including pointer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic for nested offsets.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run of `exif_from_data_fuzzer` triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` when copying more bytes than [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere allocated for an EXIF data entry. A patch was attempted in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif/exif-data.c` to:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replace unsigned int arithmetic with `size_t`[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Retrieve the byte-size of each component via `exif_format_get_size`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Check for multiplication overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`components * fmt_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Collapse the old two-step bounds checks into a single check on `doff + s`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying this patch, compilation failed with errors pointing at malformed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomments around the patch region:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:184:8[0m[39m: error: expected [0m[32m';'[0m[39m after expression[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   * has not been set yet[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ^[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:184:5[0m[39m: error: use of undeclared identifier [0m[32m'has'[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   * has not been set yet[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ^[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer: `exif_from_data_fuzzer` with libFuzzer and AddressSanitizer.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash: Heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading beyond a dynamically allocated buffer.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allocation: A [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte block allocated via `malloc` for the EXIF entry data.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Read: A [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read started exactly at byte [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m, overrunning by at least one [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace pinpoints the overflow to the calculation of data length and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset within `exif-data.c`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `entry->components` was read as a [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit unsigned long, then multiplied by the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat size implied in bytes, without overflow checks.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original code performed separate checks “tag starts past end” and “tag [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata goes past end,” but used unsigned ints and did not guard against integer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow in the multiplication.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The bug manifests when `components * format_size` exceeds the allocated size, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut still fits in [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bits, leading to an out-of-bounds copy.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changed local variables for size calculations to `size_t s, doff;` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced `size_t fmt_size, comp;`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Assigned `fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `comp = [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->components`. Early-return if either is zero.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checked `comp > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m fmt_size` to detect multiplication overflow.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Computed `s = fmt_size * comp;`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced separate bounds checks with a single check of `doff + s > [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize`, logging on failure and returning [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Left existing debug logging for the tag name placeholder.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result [0m[35m/[0m[39m Compilation Log  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compiler error cites a malformed comment around line [0m[1;36m184[0m[39m. The original [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment block[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* FIXME: should use exif_tag_get_name_in_ifd here but entry->parent [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * has not been set yet[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     was disrupted by the patch, leading to a stray `* has not been set yet` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside a comment and missing semicolon errors.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Errors indicate that the comment delimiters were not correctly preserved or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreinserted after the patch.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect the comment blocks in `exif-data.c` around the patched region to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure proper `[0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[33m...[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` syntax.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review other occurrences of format-size and component-count multiplication in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe codebase for similar overflow risks.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit the sanity checks in all data-loading paths [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_content`, `exif_data_load_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure no other [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned-int overflows or bounds-check gaps.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp5gnrk8jn[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report shows a heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s function [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` when fuzzing with `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens in a `memcpy` reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation. A patch was [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplied to `libexif/exif-data.c` that:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Added `#include <limits.h>` and changed local variables to `size_t`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Inserted checks for zero format size or component count and for multiplication [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`comp * fmt_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Replaced separate “start” and “length” boundary checks with a single check `if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite these changes, the same ASan error reoccurs at the same code location, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the boundary check did not prevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer run log shows:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     READ of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at [0m[33m...[0m[39m in exif_data_load_data_entry [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m213:3[0m[39m  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack trace climbs from `__asan_memcpy` to [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, then into other Exif parsing routines.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocation in question comes from `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, where `s` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas computed as `format_size * components`.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Patch attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libexif/exif-data.c`, around the start of `exif_data_load_data_entry`:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Introduced `size_t fmt_size, comp, s, doff;`  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Computed `fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` and `comp = [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->components;`  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Returned early if `fmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || comp == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` or `comp > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfmt_size`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Calculated `s = fmt_size * comp`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Consolidated boundary checks into:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```c[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       size_t sum = doff + s;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msum > [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch replaces two separate checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff >= size` and `s > size - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the single `sum > size` guard.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Result after patch**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Running the same fuzz testcase yields an identical ASan report at the updated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline number [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m218[0m[39m after patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The out-of-bounds read still occurs immediately after the new boundary check, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that either `doff` or `s` is being miscomputed, or that an alternate [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode path bypasses this check.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Areas for further investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic computing `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset into the buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how it differs when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata is inlined versus stored externally.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The return paths for entries with small component counts [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`<= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis stored in the IFD entry itself.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of `exif_format_get_size` for unrecognized formats and how [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`entry->components` is parsed from the input.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Higher-level routines: `exif_data_load_data_content` and [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data`, to see if they manipulate offsets or sizes before reaching [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any assumptions about alignment, padding, or endianess that could lead to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmiscalculation of lengths or offsets.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp5gnrk8jn[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run of the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness triggered an [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` during a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` call. The overflow arose when copying image metadata from the input [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, reading past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation. A patch was applied to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconvert several variables to `size_t`, add checks for multiplication overflow, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrefine inline vs. external data handling, and perform a combined bounds check [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore `memcpy`. After rebuilding with that patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash reappeared at the same code location, indicating the attempted fixes did not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invoked `exif_data_load_data_entry` with a malicious or malformed Exif[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata blob.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inside that function, the code computes the total data size `s` as `format_size *[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents` using [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit unsigned ints.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It then determines the data offset `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minline or external[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and directly [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperforms `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan reports a multi-byte heap-buffer-overflow: reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at `d + doff` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen only [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes were allocated.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack traces point to `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and show no pre-memcpy [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard that fully prevents out-of-bounds reads.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added `<limits.h>` and changed variables to `size_t fmt_size, comp, s, doff`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Computed `fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `comp = [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry->components`, then returned [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m if either zero or if `comp > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfmt_size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto prevent overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Calculated `s = fmt_size * comp`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Split handling into two branches:  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - If `s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, treat data as inline [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Else treat data as external [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replaced separate “start past end” and “goes past end” checks with a single block[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat computes `sum = doff + s` and returns [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m if `sum < doff` or `sum > size`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Left the final `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` intact, preceded by an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mASAN-instrumented log of `doff`, `s`, and buffer size.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzing after the patch still triggers a heap-buffer-overflow at the same code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and same heap region boundary [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace points to the new code at line [0m[1;36m218[0m[39m in `exif-data.c`, immediately [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore the `memcpy`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Shadow bytes confirm the read spans beyond the [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation, suggesting [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe bounds check did not catch this particular data layout.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- exif_format_get_size: verify it returns the correct byte size for each Exif [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent format and cannot under- or over-report.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- entry->components source and validation: ensure the component count read from the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata cannot bias `s` or `doff` into an invalid range.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- exif_get_long: confirm it interprets the offset field correctly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte order, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msigned vs. unsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and that large values are caught.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Branch logic for inline vs. external data: review the conditions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` vs. `s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m> [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure they cover all valid inline data cases.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Combined bounds check: examine whether casting `size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39man `unsigned int`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size_t` and comparing to `sum` may hide mismatches in signedness or maximum buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall data-load workflow: inspect surrounding calls in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_new_from_data` for any assumptions [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabout buffer length or offset alignment that could lead to mis-offset calculations.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
